WEBVTT

01:14.146 --> 01:14.987
Good morning, everyone.

01:17.251 --> 01:19.534
Y'all are still asleep, man.

01:20.275 --> 01:20.856
Good morning.

01:20.896 --> 01:27.166
Hey, I just want to introduce myself to those who are joining us, maybe at our campuses or online.

01:27.566 --> 01:28.588
My name is Jamie Smith.

01:28.668 --> 01:30.150
I am the children's pastor here.

01:30.190 --> 01:35.158
I'm blessed to be able each week to work with our kids and our families.

01:35.979 --> 01:43.250
It is my desire that our ministry partners with families to see their kids greatly influenced in their faith walks.

01:43.330 --> 01:51.759
Each week we get to see these kids really ask some awesome questions, but usually at this point they're asking for candy.

01:51.839 --> 01:55.984
So our ushers are coming at this point to hand out some dumb dums.

01:58.146 --> 01:59.208
Y'all don't want any dumb dums?

02:00.309 --> 02:03.192
I know some of my kids would want a dumb dumb at this point.

02:03.212 --> 02:09.919
But we are honored, if you would, if you have a Bible with you, would you mind taking a moment to turn to Ephesians chapter three?

02:09.959 --> 02:12.242
We're going to start in verse number 14.

02:12.450 --> 02:15.935
Before we start, I just want to tell you that I hate certain signs.

02:17.117 --> 02:18.519
I'm not talking about miraculous signs.

02:18.539 --> 02:24.909
I'm talking about signs everywhere there's signs when you go out to stores and different things.

02:25.810 --> 02:29.596
One of my least favorite signs has only one word on it.

02:30.337 --> 02:31.719
It's the sign closed.

02:33.081 --> 02:38.850
Last week, my family and I were on a trip and there's this little place that we love to go get ice cream at.

02:38.870 --> 02:41.554
And so one night after we had eaten a huge supper,

02:42.210 --> 02:43.893
The kids were like, Dad, we want ice cream.

02:44.493 --> 02:45.355
And they're like, oh, no.

02:46.356 --> 02:50.443
And so we loaded up the pilot and we started down to the ice cream place.

02:50.483 --> 02:52.546
But the problem was it was kind of late.

02:53.788 --> 03:07.348
And so as we pull up into the parking lot, parking lot's full, and as we drive by the door to get our parking spot, someone reaches to the door, grabs that sign, flips it over, and says closed.

03:09.171 --> 03:11.154
And with weeping and gnashing of teeth,

03:11.970 --> 03:16.275
We reloaded the pilot and drove back to the room and settled for a Klondike bar.

03:17.376 --> 03:18.177
Was it the same?

03:19.518 --> 03:21.500
But you know guys, here's the thing about life.

03:21.820 --> 03:26.165
We live in expectation each and every day.

03:26.585 --> 03:27.526
You want me to prove it?

03:28.047 --> 03:30.369
If you have your keys handy, pull your keys out of your pocket.

03:31.631 --> 03:38.578
Now I have expectation in my hand that when I leave this parking or leave this room today, go to the parking lot

03:38.978 --> 03:42.202
If I push this button, it's gonna unlock my door.

03:42.583 --> 03:45.467
And if I put this in the ignition and turn it, what's gonna happen?

03:46.769 --> 03:47.890
It's gonna start my car.

03:49.392 --> 03:55.561
But there's nothing more disappointing than to put that key in your car, turn it, and it sounds something like this.

03:56.102 --> 04:02.631
It's disappointing, isn't it?

04:03.973 --> 04:07.858
And see guys, in life, we encounter different kinds of disappointments like,

04:07.938 --> 04:16.066
What may upset you like I wasn't really upset that we didn't get ice cream because I'm particularly fond of soft serve rather than Mayfield, it's just me.

04:17.167 --> 04:18.468
But my kids were not happy.

04:19.649 --> 04:21.551
They wanted ice cream and they wanted it then.

04:23.192 --> 04:25.414
But it could be you have other expectations in life.

04:25.434 --> 04:32.081
Like say you're going to the doctor next week for a physical, you're not expecting for the doctor to come back in and close the door and say, hey, we need to talk.

04:33.742 --> 04:33.982
Right?

04:34.843 --> 04:37.746
You're also not expecting your phone to ring this afternoon.

04:38.754 --> 04:40.436
And someone say, Hey, are you sitting down?

04:40.876 --> 04:43.519
I need to tell you something.

04:43.539 --> 04:46.903
You see, we live every day with expectations.

04:46.943 --> 04:54.572
And the problem with expectation is that when expectations are not met, it leads to great disappointment.

04:55.433 --> 05:07.186
Chip Ingram has a formula that goes something like this, that the amount of disappointment you experience is the difference between your reality and what you expected to happen.

05:07.906 --> 05:19.743
So if I want a pizza for lunch and I leave here and I go to my favorite pizza place and the sign says, closed, I'm probably not going to be upset because we'd go somewhere else.

05:20.925 --> 05:32.081
But if I go to the parking lot and I go to start my car after I put a brand new battery in it before I left on my vacation a few weeks ago and it won't start, I will probably be upset.

05:33.242 --> 05:35.826
But now put that in terms of spirituality.

05:36.738 --> 05:40.805
But God, I prayed and you didn't give me the answer.

05:41.085 --> 05:44.591
Lord, I followed what you said, but this didn't happen.

05:45.914 --> 05:49.099
Lord, I went to church every week and you let this happen to me.

05:49.920 --> 05:50.541
Why God?

05:50.842 --> 05:51.343
Why me?

05:51.643 --> 05:52.164
Why now?

05:52.304 --> 05:52.865
Why this?

05:54.067 --> 06:00.338
In fact, you could be like this mother who on her website dedicated to her daughter said this.

06:00.898 --> 06:11.311
When we adopted Katie 24 years ago, I felt that the Lord had said he would use her to preach to the nations that God loves when she died.

06:13.734 --> 06:14.775
I'll let that sit for a moment.

06:14.795 --> 06:16.417
This young lady had a blood disorder.

06:17.358 --> 06:23.586
When she died, I felt like I had totally missed God and I didn't understand.

06:23.626 --> 06:26.610
In fact, probably much like this cup.

06:28.552 --> 06:29.874
This cup has nothing in it.

06:31.298 --> 06:44.975
When you and I encounter different frustrations in life and disappointments, especially when it comes down to God, we can be left feeling very empty and dark and alone.

06:46.117 --> 06:48.280
How many of you have had those little prayer sessions at night?

06:49.942 --> 06:53.687
When your pillow is drenched with tears and you're saying, God, where are you?

06:53.747 --> 06:56.971
Why have you left me alone?

06:57.011 --> 06:59.474
Why did you let this happen to me?

07:00.706 --> 07:01.527
You ever felt that way?

07:04.269 --> 07:06.672
You see, for many of us today, we walked into this room.

07:07.573 --> 07:10.055
We had an expectation of what church was gonna be like.

07:10.936 --> 07:19.344
For some of us, we came in and go, okay, you know, we're gonna come in, we're gonna listen, maybe somebody's seen, we'll take out some money, somebody's gonna preach, and we're gonna go home and have lunch.

07:21.846 --> 07:29.714
But can I propose to you that the way a church service can act and operate, or the way that your life can act and operate,

07:29.794 --> 07:31.916
has a lot to do with how full your cup is.

07:33.358 --> 07:36.161
Because if you don't expect a lot of things to happen, they won't.

07:37.422 --> 07:43.468
But what if, what if we need to be reminded God is not limited by our expectations?

07:44.849 --> 07:57.202
What if I were to tell you that in your Christian walk, if you're walking alone outside the power of God, outside of faith and empty, then you're matching up to your expectations.

07:57.762 --> 08:00.925
But what if I were to remind you this morning that God has not contained?

08:01.425 --> 08:04.889
He is not limited by your expectations.

08:06.370 --> 08:11.975
So if you have your Bible open, would you listen to what the Lord has to say in regards to our expectations?

08:12.576 --> 08:21.665
If you want to stand with me while we read the Scripture, that would be excellent.

08:21.685 --> 08:24.447
For this reason, I bow my knees before the Father.

08:24.467 --> 08:27.410
And this is all writing in prison.

08:28.450 --> 08:29.992
He's not praying for himself.

08:30.472 --> 08:34.437
He didn't go on to say, okay, God, I want you to bless these people, but let me out of jail.

08:34.477 --> 08:35.518
He didn't even mention that.

08:36.339 --> 08:38.381
He's praying for the Ephesian church.

08:38.421 --> 08:44.008
And he says, from whom every family in heaven and on earth derives its name.

08:44.028 --> 08:45.589
Well, why is that important?

08:45.609 --> 08:53.598
Well, in this context in chapter three, Paul is talking about the divine mystery of Christ and how you have Gentile and Jewish believers.

08:53.639 --> 08:56.722
And now he's trying to find a way to get them to get along.

08:57.378 --> 09:01.442
Because the Jews believed there were God's promised people, that's from whom where Jesus came.

09:01.862 --> 09:07.108
And now you got these people who are uncircumcised, who don't know the law, and they're having to have church together.

09:08.609 --> 09:10.711
You ever had to go to church with somebody you don't get along with?

09:12.132 --> 09:14.555
Read the New Testament because it happened the whole time.

09:15.856 --> 09:25.906
But he wanted to remind them that everyone came from God, the Father, when he created man in his image, according to his likeness, but sin martyce and pulled us down.

09:27.042 --> 09:37.438
And this is what he prays that he would grant you, which is in a dependent nature, according to the riches of his glory to be strengthened with dynamite.

09:38.440 --> 09:43.387
That's the Greek through his spirit in the inner man, where?

09:43.427 --> 09:45.130
Inside.

09:46.292 --> 09:51.260
So that Christ may dwell in your hearts through faith and that you being rooted and grounded in what?

09:52.562 --> 09:53.042
Love.

09:53.924 --> 09:55.346
So he's talking about strength.

09:55.746 --> 10:15.250
He's talking about love, may be able to understand with all the saints what is the breadth, the length, the height and the depth to know the love of Christ, which surpasses knowing to know something you don't know that you may be.

10:15.270 --> 10:16.251
I love this phrase.

10:16.291 --> 10:24.882
One of my favorite phrases in the Bible to be filled up to all the fullness of God, not empty.

10:26.498 --> 10:27.699
Now here's the great promise.

10:28.540 --> 10:35.969
Now to him who is able to do far more abundantly beyond all that we could ask or think.

10:36.129 --> 10:54.049
I can think a lot of cool things, but he's saying even what I can begin to comprehend according to the dynamite that works in us to him be the glory in the church and in Christ Jesus to all generations forever and ever.

10:54.249 --> 10:54.930
Let's pray.

10:55.202 --> 10:58.846
Father, would you light us like dynamite right now?

10:59.487 --> 11:18.327
And that your spirit may open our eyes to open our ears, that we can be reminded that no matter what situation we are in today, God, you can fill us to the fullest, that you can restore hope even in our bleakest moment.

11:18.687 --> 11:20.650
In Jesus' name, amen.

11:22.131 --> 11:24.754
So if you noticed in that first part,

11:24.962 --> 11:26.604
of the passage.

11:26.624 --> 11:33.791
The primary purpose of the indwelling spirit is to prepare us on the inside.

11:34.331 --> 11:44.562
Cy Robertson, one of the smartest men in America, would say often that if you put lipstick on a pig, it's still a pig, right?

11:45.402 --> 11:49.106
Well, guys, God wants to work in here.

11:49.967 --> 11:53.010
We can do a lot of things to work on the outside.

11:53.762 --> 11:57.609
We can make ourself look like we've got it all together, can't we?

11:58.150 --> 11:59.072
We're really good at it.

12:00.555 --> 12:02.999
But God is after your heart.

12:03.901 --> 12:14.922
In fact, it took me a long time, really long time growing up before I understood that when I was saved, God put his spirit inside of me.

12:15.603 --> 12:17.266
I was very undecipaled.

12:18.626 --> 12:25.558
But when I realized for passages like Ephesians 1, 13, that he sealed you and me with the Holy Spirit of promise.

12:25.578 --> 12:26.720
Well, what's that promise?

12:26.780 --> 12:28.583
Well, go back to the Old Testament.

12:29.004 --> 12:39.282
In Ezekiel 36, 26 and 27, he makes it clear that he wanted to take out that heart that didn't want to obey him, that didn't want to glorify him.

12:39.586 --> 12:44.132
and put his spirit inside of us to cause us to obey his commands.

12:44.152 --> 12:45.093
Well, that's important.

12:45.353 --> 12:47.236
What if you rewind the tape all the way to the beginning?

12:47.276 --> 12:50.660
God created Adam and Eve to represent him.

12:52.362 --> 12:58.290
But when they send, it marred the image of God inside of them and outside of them.

12:58.350 --> 13:02.214
So therefore we could no longer be that representation of God.

13:02.234 --> 13:05.599
However, God had a plan, right?

13:06.460 --> 13:08.242
He would send Jesus Christ.

13:08.802 --> 13:13.628
to die on the cross, to pay for our sin, but he wasn't finished with us.

13:15.230 --> 13:19.975
He didn't just save you just to get you out of hell, that's a great, great, ultimate benefit.

13:20.756 --> 13:25.562
But the right now, God wants to live in and through you, Galatians 220.

13:25.943 --> 13:27.444
I'm crucified with Christ.

13:28.446 --> 13:38.738
It's no longer I that live, but who Christ lives in me through the Holy Spirit and the life that I live, I live by faith in the Son of God who loved me.

13:38.914 --> 13:39.996
gave himself for me.

13:40.336 --> 13:44.603
He doesn't want to leave you in the same condition that he found you.

13:45.604 --> 13:48.409
Paul sent in Ephesians two that when he found you, you were dead.

13:48.469 --> 13:51.894
Dead things don't do anything because they're dead.

13:51.934 --> 13:55.099
We hit a big bug coming back from the beach.

13:56.401 --> 13:57.423
It splatted, right?

13:57.483 --> 14:02.491
You know, you ever hit one and it'd be right in front of you and you can't see around it.

14:04.734 --> 14:07.058
That dead, that bug is not coming back from the dead.

14:08.578 --> 14:15.970
But the Bible says that the same power that raised Jesus from the dead now lives inside of you and me.

14:15.990 --> 14:27.469
And Paul is praying and saying, I want them, the Ephesians church, and I believe us as well, to be strengthened with that power that only comes from his Holy Spirit.

14:29.632 --> 14:35.602
You and I have been given a great gift and he wants us to live

14:35.778 --> 14:37.260
Not just different.

14:37.520 --> 14:40.384
He wants us to live in powered lives.

14:41.685 --> 14:49.615
I mean, how is it that we can be his witnesses to our Judea and our Jerusalem and the utmost parts of the world?

14:49.735 --> 14:56.383
If we're doing it in our own power, in our own strength, if we could do it in our own strength, Jesus didn't have to die for our sins.

14:56.664 --> 15:02.290
We could just do a whole bunch of good stuff and go to heaven feeling good about ourselves, couldn't we?

15:02.310 --> 15:03.432
That's not what he meant.

15:03.972 --> 15:05.234
That's not what he intended.

15:05.506 --> 15:08.009
He wanted his glory to live through us.

15:08.971 --> 15:16.782
You know, I kind of wonder when Moses went up on the mountain and met with God and he came back with the glory of God on him.

15:18.023 --> 15:18.985
Remember what he had to do?

15:19.886 --> 15:21.488
He had to put a veil over his face.

15:22.349 --> 15:24.152
I kind of believe because it offended people.

15:26.355 --> 15:34.386
They didn't want to see the true glory of God because when we step into the light of God, it exposes our imperfections, doesn't it?

15:35.586 --> 15:41.433
But he does so because he loves us and he wants it to be exposed so it no longer has control over us.

15:43.035 --> 15:52.347
It's always confused me why someone would want to profess to believe in Jesus Christ and be saved and still live in the same muck and sin that they lived in before.

15:53.588 --> 15:54.610
Have you ever wondered that?

15:55.691 --> 15:56.812
And we don't have to.

15:56.852 --> 16:01.278
If you do a good word study in the book of Ephesians, you'll see the word walk a lot.

16:02.239 --> 16:04.562
He has called all of us to walk

16:04.866 --> 16:11.676
with Christ to walk in this partnership with the Holy Spirit, that is intended to empower us.

16:14.320 --> 16:23.434
And the truth is, as guys, we can not give people hope when ours is empty.

16:25.998 --> 16:31.026
We can't offer people something that we don't have, can we?

16:31.970 --> 16:37.198
Kind of like a few years or like a year ago, we went to Disney and I went to Hook Island.

16:38.060 --> 16:40.684
They've been there where they have the Huckleberry Finn.

16:40.704 --> 16:41.265
It's really cool.

16:41.285 --> 16:42.126
I'd never done it before.

16:42.186 --> 16:43.589
I needed a break.

16:43.609 --> 16:49.057
So we took the little fairy over and I took two of my kids with me, but it was fascinating.

16:49.077 --> 16:59.474
It was really neat, but I take these things for granted because we all live in the South and we've heard stories of the Mississippi and the Chattahoochee and, you know, we just, it's Southern, right?

16:59.874 --> 17:02.378
But what's interesting is to watch foreigners.

17:05.544 --> 17:09.050
Now I'm going to make it fun on this because they, they grew up elsewhere.

17:09.090 --> 17:10.312
They didn't grow up in the south.

17:10.332 --> 17:11.454
They didn't grow up in America.

17:11.874 --> 17:15.841
And so to hand somebody a copy of a, Hey, read the Huckleberry Finn.

17:16.302 --> 17:22.873
And they're just kind of looking at it and they're reading about steamboats and they're reading about gators and they're like, what, what is this?

17:23.855 --> 17:25.778
You see, because for you and for me,

17:26.466 --> 17:28.909
When God puts his spirit inside of us, he strengthens us.

17:29.189 --> 17:32.592
He wants something to go out from us.

17:34.474 --> 17:45.125
The primary directive of the indwelling spirit is to reveal Christ through us, to reveal Christ through us.

17:45.185 --> 17:50.331
If the primary purpose is to prepare us, he doesn't want to just stop there.

17:51.812 --> 17:53.394
It's rained a lot recently, right?

17:54.562 --> 17:57.245
We have an old sandbox on our back porch.

17:57.265 --> 17:58.346
Kids don't play with it anymore.

17:58.366 --> 17:59.087
It looks like a turtle.

17:59.367 --> 18:00.128
It's missing an eye.

18:00.148 --> 18:01.069
