18:02.650 --> 18:04.912
Well, a few weeks ago, I decided we're going to get the sand out.

18:04.932 --> 18:10.698
So I got the sand out and I leaned it up against the rail and it has this lip and the lip caught some water.

18:11.739 --> 18:12.700
And I forgot about it.

18:13.681 --> 18:15.743
Guess what happened to that water when we had the drought?

18:16.764 --> 18:17.585
It's stagnated.

18:18.326 --> 18:20.508
Stagnet water is water that gets trapped.

18:20.528 --> 18:22.290
It has no inlet and no outlet.

18:22.562 --> 18:26.086
And you and I are no different when it comes to quenching the Holy Spirit.

18:27.407 --> 18:32.253
If we want the love of God just for us and we want the spirit of God just for us, guess what?

18:32.273 --> 18:32.894
It's going to do.

18:32.954 --> 18:34.936
It's going to quench up.

18:35.377 --> 18:36.458
It's going to conquer.

18:37.118 --> 18:40.803
It's going to smell because God didn't intend for you to be a catch can.

18:40.823 --> 18:42.304
He intended you to be a conduit.

18:43.285 --> 18:48.632
He wants the spirit of God to flow through you so that you can impact this world.

18:49.412 --> 18:50.834
Look at what he said in the scripture.

18:51.266 --> 18:56.171
so that Christ may dwell in your heart through faith.

18:59.475 --> 19:00.396
Is your cup empty?

19:08.024 --> 19:18.436
If you are in despair and you are hopeless today, what if you just ask God to fill it up?

19:19.517 --> 19:20.658
Kind of a novel idea.

19:21.058 --> 19:25.664
But there's a reason for it because when we are empowered, then look, check this out.

19:25.964 --> 19:33.693
And that you being rooted, this is perfect tense and grounded perfect tense in love.

19:35.896 --> 19:43.085
I can tell somebody I love them, but until I show them that love, it, those words mean nothing.

19:44.927 --> 19:47.009
They're just words falling on deaf ears.

19:47.410 --> 19:50.834
You see, God intended that through you and through me,

19:51.074 --> 20:07.493
He's talking about the church in this context, the mystery, the divine mystery of Christ, being able to go out into the world, unless you and I are grounded in that love, unless we are operating through that strength and that power that comes from him, then we can't impact those who are around us.

20:07.533 --> 20:11.377
In fact, I would probably argue that we don't care to impact those who are around us.

20:12.098 --> 20:19.186
One of the reasons this cup gets empty is because we do too much, too much looking at us and not enough time looking at others.

20:19.714 --> 20:21.156
In fact, I heard an old story one time.

20:21.797 --> 20:28.909
There was a doctor who was struggling with depression and he's going to a psychologist and the psychologist is like, really wasn't getting anywhere with him.

20:29.449 --> 20:30.431
And so he had this idea.

20:30.451 --> 20:31.252
He said, you know what we'll do?

20:31.653 --> 20:39.906
I want you to go to McDonald's and I want you to buy a Happy Meal, go down to the train tracks and find a homeless person and give them a Happy Meal and leave.

20:39.926 --> 20:41.749
And I want you to do that over and over again.

20:42.450 --> 20:43.692
Guess what happened is depression.

20:45.675 --> 20:46.537
It alleviated it.

20:46.957 --> 20:47.378
Why?

20:48.514 --> 20:49.856
because he needed an outlet.

20:51.959 --> 20:59.408
Rather than storing it up for a safe day, he needed somewhere to let that thing be expressed.

20:59.428 --> 21:08.020
Because until we do that, the experience of love must be realized inside of us before it can be expressed to other men.

21:10.163 --> 21:10.984
You see that, right?

21:13.006 --> 21:15.730
I can't love my children until I love my wife well.

21:18.050 --> 21:28.044
I truly believe, and Paul talks about this in Ephesians later in the book, he talks about how man can't really love his wife unless he loves himself.

21:29.366 --> 21:32.330
Well, I would argue I can't love my kids unless I love my wife.

21:33.051 --> 21:40.722
The greatest gift I can give to my kids is the loving relationship that I have with my wife, because it gives them security.

21:41.506 --> 21:44.710
When you're feeling hopeless and in despair, you've lost your security.

21:44.730 --> 21:45.691
You've lost your footing.

21:45.971 --> 21:47.313
You've lost your groundedness.

21:47.573 --> 21:58.565
You need to be reminded that God has promised that He would fill you with the Spirit to strengthen you, to ground and root you in His love.

21:58.585 --> 22:00.527
Because it's kind of like this.

22:00.587 --> 22:02.109
I've got a couple more cups up here.

22:03.911 --> 22:05.933
Why don't you think about capacity for a moment?

22:05.993 --> 22:10.098
Now, Tony Evans told a great illustration years ago

22:10.178 --> 22:18.406
that I have robbed, I love this illustration, but he was talking about God and being filled to the full, being like the Pacific Ocean.

22:19.387 --> 22:20.728
There's so much of God.

22:21.989 --> 22:32.159
But if my expectation is maybe say the size of a thimble, and I go down to the Pacific Ocean and I dip that thimble into the ocean, how much of God am I gonna get?

22:34.381 --> 22:34.701
How much?

22:35.782 --> 22:39.826
A thimble's worth, because that's the capacity of the container, right?

22:40.130 --> 22:41.171
Well, what if I took this?

22:41.231 --> 22:46.336
This is what I have called a jelly bean holder because it's what we gave to the kids back at Easter.

22:46.356 --> 22:47.297
This held jelly beans.

22:47.838 --> 22:53.884
It's really insulting in a way because it's not a lot of jelly beans can hold in this.

22:54.424 --> 22:59.550
But if I went down to the ocean and dipped this into the water, how much of the water can I get?

22:59.570 --> 23:02.512
A jelly bean holder's work.

23:02.993 --> 23:08.018
If I take this cup that I've been showing you and I go down to the Pacific Ocean and I dip it, how much can I get?

23:09.058 --> 23:10.721
because that's my capacity.

23:11.261 --> 23:15.988
And I can keep going on all the way up to, y'all may not know this, but I do know how to operate an 18-wheeler.

23:16.409 --> 23:17.651
It's just not lasting to do it.

23:18.332 --> 23:19.133
So I won't prove it.

23:20.115 --> 23:26.164
But if I took and hooked it up to a tanker and drove down to the Pacific Ocean and filled it up with water, how much water will it hold?

23:27.125 --> 23:27.947
A tanker full.

23:28.387 --> 23:29.429
The point is this.

23:30.711 --> 23:33.595
And now, let me, where I got a quote, where's my quote?

23:33.615 --> 23:34.977
Oh, I put it in here, excuse me.

23:36.359 --> 23:38.162
This is what Tony Evans

23:38.370 --> 23:47.579
said at the end of that, how can you ask God who made the Pacific Ocean to give you more than your thimble's worth that of your commitment will allow?

23:47.619 --> 23:59.411
The reason God allows us to go through trials and tribulations is so that our capacity will increase so that we can get more and we can get more.

23:59.431 --> 24:06.738
And then let me ask you this, what if, what if this had water in it and I started pouring it in and it started running over.

24:09.122 --> 24:09.422
Let's see.

24:11.105 --> 24:12.287
Check this out.

24:12.307 --> 24:17.955
The primary experience of the indwelling spirit is to witness his power's work.

24:17.975 --> 24:18.435
Is that word?

24:19.877 --> 24:20.538
Beyond?

24:21.520 --> 24:31.634
Because he said in the word, now to him who is able to do far more abundantly beyond all that we ask or think according to his what?

24:32.194 --> 24:35.117
His power again, he said, he wanted to be strengthened by the power of the Holy Spirit.

24:35.137 --> 24:38.801
Now he's saying that you would be able to do far more abundantly.

24:38.821 --> 24:44.628
Did Jesus not tell his disciples that they would do greater things than he did in the upper room?

24:46.130 --> 24:47.752
So why is that not true today?

24:49.193 --> 24:54.739
Why is it that oftentimes we approach our Christian walk as just, well, it's just my thing to do.

24:55.460 --> 25:00.626
It's like if I wanted to tell somebody about Jesus and I went up to him and said, hey, Jesus is the best thing that ever happened to you.

25:01.826 --> 25:02.647
Would you believe me?

25:04.009 --> 25:17.327
No, but when I truly have grasped the understanding and experience the love and the power of God, I don't just go up to somebody and say, I'm like, dude, Jesus is the best thing that can happen to your life.

25:18.789 --> 25:24.256
There is no power of God manifested when I can accomplish something in my own strength.

25:28.462 --> 25:31.506
Far more than we can ask.

25:31.810 --> 25:50.319
I can imagine a lot of things, but when I'm in desperate need, when I'm in a hopeless situation, I need to know that the God of the universe cares enough about me that He would fill me back to the full.

25:55.727 --> 26:00.114
As Paul said, when I'm weak, that's when I'm strong.

26:01.666 --> 26:05.131
See, we can come in and we can have all that exterior looking great.

26:05.652 --> 26:12.582
We can put on the smiles, we can carry our Ryrie study Bible that's about this thick with all the study notes we've ever heard.

26:14.785 --> 26:23.117
But when my heart is rotten and discouraged and down and out, the only solution is Jesus.

26:25.120 --> 26:26.642
Years ago, I did an illustration.

26:26.850 --> 26:28.372
And it didn't, I didn't even attend to this.

26:28.452 --> 26:32.636
I went to the store and I bought the perfect red delicious apple.

26:33.257 --> 26:34.358
I love crispy apples.

26:34.618 --> 26:36.260
Oh gosh, so good.

26:36.280 --> 26:37.461
I love honey crisp now.

26:37.482 --> 26:39.103
That's my favorite.

26:39.123 --> 26:43.328
But I bought the, I mean, this thing was like this big and I mean, it had been buffed to a shine.

26:43.348 --> 26:44.950
There wasn't a spot.

26:44.970 --> 26:46.251
There wasn't a blemish on it.

26:46.651 --> 26:52.518
And I went to speak to some young upcoming pastors about, you know, this is where your core values are.

26:52.578 --> 26:54.140
And then that's expressed in the skin.

26:55.041 --> 26:56.402
I went to cut that apple.

26:57.538 --> 26:59.881
And it was rotten.

26:59.901 --> 27:00.962
It was black.

27:00.982 --> 27:04.326
I wish I can't recreate that because it just happened by chance.

27:05.847 --> 27:07.569
I took that moment to show up and said, you know what?

27:07.609 --> 27:09.812
It doesn't matter what the outside looks like.

27:09.852 --> 27:11.534
If this is the inside, you're hopeless.

27:13.836 --> 27:15.198
My question to you is this.

27:15.738 --> 27:17.120
What if you re-dreamed again?

27:18.461 --> 27:21.144
What if you dreamed a God-sized dream in your life?

27:22.165 --> 27:26.290
Maybe those test results, I'm not sure how they'll play out, but I do know who's got,

27:26.530 --> 27:28.091
my life in their, in his hands.

27:29.193 --> 27:30.173
What if I said, you know what God?

27:30.193 --> 27:35.579
I'm going to trust you to do far beyond anything I can possibly think or imagine.

27:35.599 --> 27:44.267
What if I were this morning to take whatever expectations I have and surrender them to the Lord?

27:44.907 --> 27:51.153
Cause that formula that said that disappointment is equal to reality minus expectation.

27:51.554 --> 27:56.018
You can really change that to say that joy equals reality.

27:56.162 --> 27:57.484
minus expectation.

27:59.107 --> 28:09.162
When I trust that the Lord has my life in his hands, then there are things that I can't even possibly dream about that God can do in and through my life.

28:09.863 --> 28:11.666
So would you bow your heads with me this morning?

28:12.568 --> 28:16.714
And I'll ask a couple of things and then we're gonna have our invitation.

28:17.415 --> 28:18.477
But the first one is this.

28:19.238 --> 28:21.802
Have you come in here this morning feeling empty like this cup?

28:23.605 --> 28:24.306
Hopeless?

28:25.570 --> 28:28.033
alone, like God's left you.

28:29.654 --> 28:31.276
I'm here to tell you, He hasn't left you.

28:32.918 --> 28:36.342
See, because if we have trusted Christ as our Savior, He's as close as our heart, isn't He?

28:37.122 --> 28:43.029
He put Him inside of us, so He's there with us, correct?

28:43.049 --> 28:49.756
What I want to ask this morning is the same thing that Paul asked in his prayer, that you would be filled to the full.

28:50.617 --> 28:55.442
If that's you this morning and you just want to be prayed for, and no one's looking around, just slip your hand up and put it back down.

28:59.938 --> 29:00.258
Thank you.

29:01.520 --> 29:08.551
Now, if you don't know Jesus Christ as your Savior, all you have to do is receive Him this morning.

29:10.634 --> 29:22.351
He died on the cross to pay your sin death, to rescue you from death, was raised again to prove that He had beat sin and death and can grant you and me eternal life.

29:23.293 --> 29:26.217
If that's you this morning, would you trust Him?

29:26.918 --> 29:29.522
I'm going to be down at the front with Brandon.

29:30.658 --> 29:36.286
If you want to be prayed for, if you want to talk to somebody a little bit more about that, maybe you've been saved and you'd like to be baptized.

29:38.128 --> 29:42.374
To obey Christ, to obey Him at His Word, you'd like to come forward and be considered for baptism.

29:42.795 --> 29:44.457
We'll be up here for that as well.

29:44.497 --> 29:48.763
If you want to join Concord, now's the time.

29:49.524 --> 29:50.325
Make this your home.

29:51.086 --> 29:53.390
Put down your roots here.

29:53.810 --> 29:56.294
Find a place to connect and serve.

29:56.314 --> 29:59.378
And we'd love to talk to you about that.

29:59.970 --> 30:03.755
Father, as we come to this invitation, Lord, we surrender it to you.

30:04.095 --> 30:08.040
God, there were hands that went up, and I just pray, Father, that whatever their need is.

30:08.060 --> 30:11.524
God, let them surrender that expectation to you.

30:12.145 --> 30:13.487
We can't control reality.

30:14.188 --> 30:17.812
We can't even control outcomes, but we can control our hope.

30:18.893 --> 30:20.856
For some of us, it's easy to look at the negative.

30:21.396 --> 30:29.106
But what we ask this morning, God, is that you would work in us to see where you're at work and that you would touch us in Jesus' name.

30:30.466 --> 30:32.013
Would you stand with me as we sing?

30:32.495 --> 30:36.754
And if any of those conditions fit you this morning, we'll be up here at the front waiting on you to come.

